Description: Think Christmas 4 Urself or that special sum1 "So you want to be a rock and roll star, then listen now to what I say. Just get an electric guitar and take some time and learn how to play",,,, Roger McGuinn & Chris Hillman, aka The Byrds Well first the kid wanted to,,,, and then it was on to something else,,,, It's all good,,,,consequence: "Your's is no disgrace" (Yes) I have to offer up for sale at auction, this "cherry" or "near mint" used guitar as shown: a Diamond Series Schecter S-1 Elite . It is clean and beautiful S1 Elite Review by Guitaplaya27 Mag July 10 2006 "The S-1 Elite is a set-neck double cutaway with a figured maple top on it's mahogany body. The neck is 3-piece mahogany with a 22-jumbo fret keyboard and Gothic cross inlays. It's Tone Pros Bridge system strings through the body for increased sustain and the fullest tone. Other features include Grover tuners, Ducan Design H101 pickups and abalone binding . The S-1 Elite simply looks and plays like nothing else!" on a 10 scale Features- 9.4Sound- 9.5Action- 9.5Reliability- 9.3Impression- 9.3______________ Reviewer gave it - 9.4 but wait,,,,,,,,,,,,, there is more,,,, Features: this guitar has a unique sound for a guitar . It can play metal, punk and blues without changing a setting on your amp. It has 22 jumbo frets. The pickups are Seymour Duncan designed HB 102/SC 102 with a tab that you can pull up to split the coils for a single coil sound. Great feature. 3 way switch selector, one volume, one tone and one-tab button/volume for the single coil sound. Grover tuners that keep it in tune. Mahogany/quilted maple body. Mahogany/rosewood neck. Black/Chrome hardware. Black Cherry finish,,,,the finish is artwork, this guitar has no problems. Comes with the Road Runner soft-shelled padded & zippered case and with strap shown Don't forget who you are. You're a Rock and Roll star!
Title: Schecter Diamond Series S-1 Elite, Black Cherry, "tis Cherry", Think Christmas
